      "writtenOn": "2020-10-26T20:21:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "These are applied to static libraries. In this case, these applies especially to static libraries.\n\nIn general, marking a static library \"X_available\" means that only modules / binaries in X can use/link to this static library. So, without this change, any modules / binaries in ramdisk or vendor_ramdisk can\u0027t link statically to libclang_rt.*.\n\nWhat\u0027s more, in ramdisk and vendor_ramdisk, only static binaries can be run, because there\u0027s no linker there.\n\n(ccross please CMIIW)",
      "parentUuid": "e11b5182_bbccf8e5",
